If you look at the CB filter sump it has a bypass valve in it just for this
reason (thick oil). Then of course if you use a multi grade oil, you should
have no problems to begin with. I will be posting a link tonight to describe
oil viscosities and HOW multi grade oils work. This link also tells the pour
point and the burn point and also tells you zinc and sulfur content and
there uses in motor oil. It list at least 10 different brands of oils, so
you can decide which is best for you. I personally use Valvoline racing
which is good for the way I drive (high rpms and abusive) and learned that
this is the best for me, but looking at the chart it is not good for the by
the book, shift at 2000 rpmer's.

ronnie     trying hard to blow one up

